To solve \(m^{2}-4m+4=8\), first bring all terms to one side:
\[
m^{2}-4m+4-8=0
\;\Longrightarrow\;
m^{2}-4m-4=0.
\]
Apply the quadratic formula \(m=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\) with \(a=1,\;b=-4,\;c=-4\):
\[
m=\frac{-(-4)\pm\sqrt{(-4)^2-4\cdot1\cdot(-4)}}{2\cdot1}
=\frac{4\pm\sqrt{16+16}}{2}
=\frac{4\pm\sqrt{32}}{2}
=\frac{4\pm4\sqrt2}{2}
=2\pm2\sqrt2.
\]
So the solutions are
\[
\boxed{m=2+2\sqrt2\quad\text{or}\quad m=2-2\sqrt2.}
\]
